# pyenv
#   For a library or app, you might want to share your .python-version if you use pyenv
#   But for a user, it's often personal
#.python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#598, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in version control.
#   However, in case of collaboration, if used, it can be useful to share.
#Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, poetry.lock can be shared but sometimes ignored
#poetry.lock

# pdm
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, pdm.lock can be shared but sometimes ignored
#pdm.lock

